The Pearson correlation between human assessments and few-shot prompt-based automated evaluations showed weak positive correlations: 0.24 (helpfulness), 0.12 (relevance), and 0.19 (faithfulness). Inter-annotator reliability, measured on the overlapping 10% of the responses from 3 annotators using Krippendorff's alpha, indicated strong agreement with scores of 0.71 (helpfulness), 0.77 (relevance), and 0.61 (faithfulness).